Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Overview of Approaches in Computational Chemistry", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814540682358514*^9, 3.814540687340576*^9}, {
  3.8145415436773176`*^9, 3.814541561480219*^9}, {3.814541714736204*^9, 
  3.8145417177206464`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a5b8fd15-849a-4c24-9319-\
4f88fa5dfefe"],

Cell["\<\
There are now many approaches in computational chemistry that may or may not \
be well-suited to the system you wish to investigate. This lesson won\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]t come close to covering all of these methods, but we\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]ll cover some of the most common techniques and the choices \
associated with each.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814546882956972*^9, 3.8145468878507743`*^9}, {
  3.814546932703314*^9, 
  3.814547064452756*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"89476085-f226-4d52-a8d9-\
ac9a6985de27"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Choose a Method", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8145415744472294`*^9, 3.8145415756663017`*^9}, {
  3.814541609647438*^9, 
  3.814541610268694*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"15628e51-5800-447a-96d9-\
2a014dc0cf52"],

Cell["\<\
There are a multitude of approaches for calculating both static structures \
and properties and time-dependent dynamics of systems. A few of them are \
listed here:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8145471974791574`*^9, 3.8145472156399765`*^9}, {
  3.814547370590464*^9, 3.814547375683445*^9}, {3.8145474912076902`*^9, 
  3.814547525186761*^9}, {3.814547642623423*^9, 
  3.8145476735183992`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"12272d06-7417-4b03-841b-\
c9aa5a396010"],

Cell["\<\
Hartree-Fock calculations \[Dash] we\[CloseCurlyQuote]ve already discussed \
the Hartree-Fock method several times in this course. Because this method \
only accounts for electron correlation relating to spin, \
it\[CloseCurlyQuote]s generally not very accurate and is not typically used \
in research anymore. However, as mentioned, the method forms the basis for \
other, more accurate approaches.\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8145476794063454`*^9, 3.81454787641941*^9}, {
  3.8145479879284935`*^9, 
  3.8145480226796846`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"fa72d01f-349f-4c00-b2c3-\
b4318f436436"],

Cell["\<\
M\[OSlash]ller\[Dash]Plesset perturbation theory \[Dash] these approaches \
involve perturbative corrections to the Hartree-Fock method,\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8145476794063454`*^9, 3.814547884257888*^9}, {
  3.814548011692357*^9, 3.814548040560336*^9}, {3.8145480958761063`*^9, 
  3.814548107944996*^9}, {3.8145483773494434`*^9, 3.814548432738103*^9}, {
  3.814548553703367*^9, 3.8145485558911667`*^9}, {3.814548676432017*^9, 
