      FormBox["\"pVQZ\"", TraditionalForm]}, {4, 
      FormBox["\"pV5Z\"", TraditionalForm]}}, {{1, 
      FormBox[
      "\"\\!\\(\\*SubscriptBox[StyleBox[\\\"E\\\",FontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"], \
\\\"CBS\\\"]\\)\"", TraditionalForm]}}},
  TicksStyle->Directive[
    GrayLevel[0], 
    Thickness[Large]]]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814882083907774*^9, 3.81488220629412*^9}, {
  3.81488226502032*^9, 3.8148823340342803`*^9}},
 CellLabel->"Out[82]=",ExpressionUUID->"1b427a51-d3d4-4d60-ae39-3f36cce4831b"]
}, {2}]],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Figure 12.4.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " Example of the extrapolation of the complete-basis-set energy ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    SubscriptBox["E", "CBS"], ")"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f1042926-331f-49b5-9b30-ef77f27e4b2c"],
 " using the correlation-consistent basis sets."
}], "Affiliation",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.809435027311596*^9, 3.8094350763900714`*^9}, {
   3.80943583474421*^9, 3.8094358359299717`*^9}, {3.8094472165104203`*^9, 
   3.809447281165168*^9}, {3.810054221304062*^9, 3.8100542409148703`*^9}, {
   3.8101125924447937`*^9, 3.8101126426025887`*^9}, {3.8101127071459217`*^9, 
   3.810112714050138*^9}, {3.810115126505663*^9, 3.810115154403865*^9}, {
   3.8101152097595587`*^9, 3.8101152368678613`*^9}, {3.8104844563968916`*^9, 
   3.8104844576598825`*^9}, {3.81193141565689*^9, 3.8119315300297594`*^9}, {
   3.8119337071325006`*^9, 3.811933740644105*^9}, {3.8119343804898696`*^9, 
   3.811934419448634*^9}, {3.811934465780332*^9, 3.8119344672733955`*^9}, {
   3.8119350679013205`*^9, 3.811935086595256*^9}, {3.814614320484557*^9, 
   3.814614322854318*^9}, {3.814614379345688*^9, 3.8146144110438213`*^9}, {
   3.8148824470841537`*^9, 3.814882507024972*^9}, {3.8148904606479645`*^9, 
   3.8148904607697334`*^9}, 
   3.9392061477700787`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"947940f2-37bf-4f32-a1ba-\
7c69d99ec3ce"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Additional Basis Sets", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8148832147579517`*^9, 
  3.8148832199581423`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"2d3b3802-21ae-47d5-928d-\
f9e1ef718513"],

Cell["\<\
There are far too many basis sets to cover all of them here, but we will \
briefly introduce a few additional popular classes of basis sets. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8148832218142276`*^9, 3.8148832641808605`*^9}, {
  3.8148832941947355`*^9, 3.814883300774392*^9}, {3.8148833347841854`*^9, 
  3.8148834852584157`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"960c0a81-9f9b-4cf7-91f3-\
0a5b0093dab8"],

Cell["\<\
The so-called Karlsruhe basis sets are likewise split-valence double- or \
triple-zeta basis sets, but they are optimized based on achieving the lowest \
possible energy (which, remember, in the variational method, is another way \
of saying the most accurate energy). They are given the prefix def2, for \
example def2-TZVP (def2 triple-zeta valence with polarization) or def2-QZVPPD \
(def2 quadruple-zeta valence with double polarization and diffuse functions). \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814883487774479*^9, 
  3.814883569181506*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"cdb5af5d-001f-4a3d-b1e3-\
07d0c9c02477"],

Cell["\<\
There are also basis sets that have been optimized for DFT rather than \
post-Hartree-Fock (MP2, CCSD(T), etc.) methods. One popular class of these \
basis sets are the polarization-consistent (pc) basis sets developed by \
Jensen and co-workers. These are designed to enable a similar \
complete-basis-set extrapolation to that for the cc basis sets, in this case \
using DFT instead of a post-Hartree-Fock method.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8148835739119067`*^9, 
  3.8148836965032253`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"80b2634b-e0c5-4df6-9ae3-\
b7d0d716cff6"],

Cell["\<\
Finally, a brief note about heavier atomic elements: when the atomic number \
is larger, as in many transition metals, relativistic effects become \
important in describing the behavior of the electrons, and these are not \
accounted for in typical computational chemistry approaches. Therefore, for \
larger atoms, an effective core potential (ECP) that empirically accounts for \
relativistic effects is typically incorporated into the basis set. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8148837144513817`*^9, 
  3.8148838297136736`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"19a8a975-834a-4666-b5c2-\
187444aafaa3"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Post Hartree-Fock Methods - Overview", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8148869090450144`*^9, 
  3.8148869155465193`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"2bfa72b9-9b45-4577-b784-\
27e59e79739b"],

Cell["\<\
We already discussed briefly in the introduction some of the so-called post \
Hartree-Fock methods such as MP2 and CCSD(T). Here we will give a little more \
information about the general approach taken by these methods.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8148869183001647`*^9, 
  3.81488696216323*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e7036533-1c77-421e-b85a-\
b31764ff7e22"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Failings of the Hartree-Fock Method", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814886973617584*^9, 
  3.8148869780649643`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"715ac81c-c1b6-47e0-8979-\
64f551231b21"],

Cell["\<\
As we have already discussed, the Hartree-Fock method assumes that (excluding \
spin) the behavior of the electrons is not correlated, which allows us to \
write the wavefunction as an antisymmetrized product of the individual \
spin-orbital wavefunctions given by the Slater determinant.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8148869803324327`*^9, 3.814887067264869*^9}, {
  3.814887137188528*^9, 
  3.8148871409222*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1faa670c-9cd8-4153-981d-9d3c851e3550"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox["\[Psi]", "Slater"], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{"1", ",", "2", ",", "...", ",", 
     StyleBox["N",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]}], ")"}]}], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox["1", 
    SqrtBox[
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["N",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "!"}]]], 
   RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", GridBox[{
      {
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["\[Chi]", "1"], 
        RowBox[{"(", "1", ")"}]}], 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["\[Chi]", "2"], 
        RowBox[{"(", "1", ")"}]}], "...", 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["\[Chi]", 
         StyleBox["N",
          FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
        RowBox[{"(", "1", ")"}]}]},
      {
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["\[Chi]", "1"], 
        RowBox[{"(", "2", ")"}]}], 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["\[Chi]", "2"], 
        RowBox[{"(", "2", ")"}]}], "...", 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["\[Chi]", 
         StyleBox["N",
          FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
        RowBox[{"(", "2", ")"}]}]},
      {"...", "...", "...", "..."},
      {
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["\[Chi]", "1"], 
        RowBox[{"(", 
         StyleBox["N",
          FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}]}], 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["\[Chi]", "2"], 
        RowBox[{"(", 
         StyleBox["N",
          FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}]}], "...", 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["\[Chi]", 
         StyleBox["N",
          FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
        RowBox[{"(", 
         StyleBox["N",
          FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}]}]}
     }], "\[NoBreak]\[NoBreak]", 
    "\[RightBracketingBar]"}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.810112811439228*^9, 3.8101128248442793`*^9}, {
   3.810479494926491*^9, 3.8104795038498344`*^9}, {3.810479572543576*^9, 
   3.8104796147383184`*^9}, {3.8104802055659895`*^9, 
   3.8104802433915305`*^9}, {3.8104802785189395`*^9, 
   3.8104802814214115`*^9}, {3.8109915300785556`*^9, 
   3.8109916793993816`*^9}, {3.810991710031681*^9, 3.8109918292023373`*^9}, {
   3.810994488524798*^9, 3.810994499853472*^9}, {3.8109948928195066`*^9, 
   3.8109948950763626`*^9}, {3.8109949491606197`*^9, 3.810995087249513*^9}, {
   3.8109951188614283`*^9, 3.8109951226144466`*^9}, {3.8115998145208507`*^9, 
   3.8115999093225703`*^9}, 3.8119468581508093`*^9, {3.8126173912859564`*^9, 
   3.8126174353481674`*^9}, {3.812617986792708*^9, 3.812617987701547*^9}, {
   3.8126194925193796`*^9, 3.812619503416272*^9}, {3.812619551056244*^9, 
   3.812619564308283*^9}, {3.812619992990877*^9, 3.8126200208718753`*^9}, 
   3.8126201248430705`*^9, {3.812620163920018*^9, 3.8126201669704065`*^9}, {
   3.8126204678526173`*^9, 3.8126204826728334`*^9}, {3.8126205155312433`*^9, 
   3.81262057853043*^9}, {3.812620660711446*^9, 3.812620661159943*^9}, {
   3.8126208302516937`*^9, 3.8126208466299543`*^9}, {3.812620980916898*^9, 
   3.8126209810859137`*^9}, 3.8126287856964226`*^9, {3.812629271581931*^9, 
   3.8126292755855017`*^9}, {3.8126293423208475`*^9, 3.812629351460653*^9}, {
   3.8126294501142464`*^9, 3.8126295143102984`*^9}, {3.8126295903225517`*^9, 
   3.812629649928158*^9}, {3.8126296948107743`*^9, 3.812629695292021*^9}, {
   3.8126300281015587`*^9, 3.81263005763659*^9}, {3.812630089427315*^9, 
   3.8126301336773043`*^9}, {3.8126301819630384`*^9, 3.8126302619488583`*^9}, 
   3.8126308057010317`*^9, {3.8126309591900663`*^9, 3.8126309614862156`*^9}, {
   3.8126311639264126`*^9, 3.812631166180791*^9}, {3.814887488579198*^9, 
   3.814887489718397*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"76fe6776-a155-4312-815b-\
5391e525fcae"],

Cell["\<\
Remember that in this picture, each electron interacts only with the average \
charge distribution of all of the other electrons given by the effective \
potential. Thus, correlated interactions between electrons are not accounted \
for, leading to the so-called correlation energy error. Remember that \
dispersion interactions are the result of electron correlation, so clearly \
this error can be rather substantial and even lead to wholly incorrect \
predictions about the structure and behavior of molecules.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814887169827781*^9, 3.8148871751814356`*^9}, {
  3.8148872136657944`*^9, 3.814887408149313*^9}, {3.8148920291197176`*^9, 
  3.8148920300904007`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"45d4d841-97a4-4def-aa46-\
ae1282b0edef"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Linear Combination of Slater Determinants", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.81488748317336*^9, 
  3.814887509752577*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b80add1c-2431-49cd-bd76-\
38aeb60be57e"],

Cell["\<\
Although the single-Slater-determinant wavefunction is not exact, it is \
properly antisymmetrized. In principle, we can write the exact wavefunction \
as a linear combination of many different Slater-determinant wavefunctions\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814887513094187*^9, 
  3.8148876244629183`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"86e8867a-d707-45aa-b515-\
37c9c7a5e9ce"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SubscriptBox["\[Psi]", "exact"], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
    StyleBox["i",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   SubscriptBox["\[Psi]", 
    SubscriptBox["Slater", 
     StyleBox["i",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]]]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8148876318461924`*^9, 3.8148876812923756`*^9}, {
  3.8148879015224133`*^9, 
  3.8148879096330404`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3affa2b6-3002-423e-b588-\
40852273d891"],

Cell["\<\
But what would be the other Slater determinants besides the one from \
Hartree-Fock theory? Well, in short, they are excited-state functions, that \
is, wavefunctions in which one or more of the electrons are not in the \
ground-state molecular orbitals. The technique of configuration interaction \
(CI) involves taking all of the possible combinations of electron \
configurations for a given basis set, but it\[CloseCurlyQuote]s so \
computationally intensive as to be impractical for all but the smallest \
systems.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814887688347639*^9, 3.8148877589998255`*^9}, {
  3.814887789151481*^9, 3.8148878388437786`*^9}, {3.814888806888939*^9, 
  3.81488882620113*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a4184816-c110-4377-9b9c-\
c3518e97230e"],

Cell["\<\
Typically, the types of excitations are grouped together based on the number \
of excited (i.e., non-ground-state) electrons,\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.81488787085227*^9, 
  3.814887926390113*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"024f7ea3-231f-4bc5-b345-\
5ade3a3adee2"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", "\[Psi]"}], 
            "\[RightAngleBracket]"}], "=", 
           RowBox[{
            SubscriptBox[
             StyleBox["c",
              FontSlant->"Italic"], "0"], 
            RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
             SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "0"]}]}]}], "\[RightAngleBracket]"}], "+", 
         RowBox[{"\[Sum]", 
          RowBox[{
           SubsuperscriptBox[
            StyleBox["c",
             FontSlant->"Italic"], 
            StyleBox["i",
             FontSlant->"Italic"], 
            StyleBox["a",
             FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
           RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
            SubsuperscriptBox["\[Phi]", 
             StyleBox["i",
              FontSlant->"Italic"], 
             StyleBox["a",
              FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]}]}]}], "\[RightAngleBracket]"}], "+", 
       RowBox[{"\[Sum]", 
        RowBox[{
         SubsuperscriptBox[
          StyleBox["c",
           FontSlant->"Italic"], 
          StyleBox["ij",
           FontSlant->"Italic"], 
          StyleBox["ab",
           FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
         RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
          SubsuperscriptBox["\[Phi]", 
           StyleBox["ij",
            FontSlant->"Italic"], 
           StyleBox["ab",
            FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]}]}]}], "\[RightAngleBracket]"}], "+", 
     RowBox[{"\[Sum]", 
      RowBox[{
       SubsuperscriptBox[
        StyleBox["c",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], 
        StyleBox["ijk",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], 
        StyleBox["abc",
         FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
       RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
        SubsuperscriptBox["\[Phi]", 
         StyleBox["ijk",
          FontSlant->"Italic"], 
         StyleBox["abc",
          FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]}]}]}], "\[RightAngleBracket]"}], "+"}], 
  "..."}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8148876318461924`*^9, 3.8148876812923756`*^9}, {
  3.8148879015224133`*^9, 3.8148880876199646`*^9}, {3.8148881195936656`*^9, 
  3.81488812022952*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c54af320-792b-47dd-995a-\
a69428fa3c4f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
    SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "0"]}], "\[RightAngleBracket]"}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8148876318461924`*^9, 3.8148876812923756`*^9}, {
   3.8148879015224133`*^9, 3.8148880876199646`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "b31a5219-5df8-4266-a0de-2afe9fa390cc"],
 " is the reference ground-state Slater determinant from HF theory, and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
    SubsuperscriptBox["\[Phi]", 
     StyleBox[
      RowBox[{"ijk", "..."}],
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox[
      RowBox[{"abc", "..."}],
      FontSlant->"Italic"]]}], "\[RightAngleBracket]"}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8148876318461924`*^9, 3.8148876812923756`*^9}, {
   3.8148879015224133`*^9, 3.8148880876199646`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "4fe6babf-a6b1-40f9-b4a8-a88a6dc7b041"],
 " represents a Slater determinant where the orbitals ",
 StyleBox["i",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["j",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["k",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", ... have been replaced with the orbitals ",
 StyleBox["a",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["b",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["c",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", ... The second term in equation (10) represents single excitations, the \
third term represents double excitations, and so on. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8148880899882774`*^9, 
  3.814888251764385*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"26815c5a-d52c-4fd7-9f2a-\
9a9f9cbcff5a"],

Cell["\<\
The exact method to determine the coefficients and determinants in equation \
(10) becomes quite complicated. As mentioned, MP2 uses a variational \
treatment to determine the coefficients, and it turns out that the \
second-order correction to the energy depends only on the double excitation \
terms. Coupled-cluster calculations also involve a specific combination of \
excitations given by excitation operators.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814888347028788*^9, 3.8148885002212505`*^9}, {
  3.8148888556505985`*^9, 3.8148888638407707`*^9}, {3.8148922397968583`*^9, 
  3.814892248936384*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d6c5fc07-b1af-4bbc-a8ee-\
cdf7889ba00f"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Density Functional Theory", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8148885101456738`*^9, 
  3.814888513027212*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"09383368-5e53-4b60-af9b-\
4811163fe0f7"],

Cell["\<\
We will now provide a brief overview of density functional theory (DFT). \
Because the fundamental assumptions of DFT are quite different from those of \
Hartree-Fock theory, we begin with an introduction to the underlying \
principles.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8149432957980175`*^9, 
  3.814943362904169*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"31758231-41a7-4fce-b101-\
4ab9ac11a332"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Hohenberg-Kohn Theorems", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814943366530513*^9, 
  3.8149433757980003`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3bcd7947-fba3-41ab-b613-\
cd1880f76f2b"],

Cell["\<\
The two theorems of Hohenberg and Kohn, formulated in the 1960s, represent \
the starting point for DFT. The basic idea is that the electronic \
wavefunction can be replaced by an electron density.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814943378937031*^9, 
  3.814943430110649*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c02763c2-54a9-4eb6-ad4b-\
6fcdbad8320c"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Theorem 1", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8149434332144375`*^9, 3.8149434342593064`*^9}, {
  3.8149439918292623`*^9, 
  3.814943993429759*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"05e39ebf-a7cb-4a7e-989d-\
79fcf07dce6f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "For a system of electrons moving in an external potential ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["v", "ext"], "(", 
    StyleBox["r",
     FontWeight->"Bold"], ")"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "aed57a5a-0117-4d0a-a549-172a8516c4f9"],
 ", the potential is uniquely determined by the electron density ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[Rho]", "(", 
    StyleBox["r",
     FontWeight->"Bold"], ")"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4142052c-6b3a-42cf-aa0a-ed0cbae9f923"],
 ". "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814943471723522*^9, 3.8149434955022087`*^9}, {
   3.81494353272723*^9, 3.814943598422922*^9}, {3.814943640475416*^9, 
   3.814943685844777*^9}, {3.8149438249387145`*^9, 3.8149438378648567`*^9}, 
   3.814943872082255*^9, {3.814945006459198*^9, 
   3.814945010447977*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ac66d38b-d15d-40f0-8dd4-\
5b9f5c37c851"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In more simple language, one might say that the ground-state properties of \
a system of electrons are given by the electron density function ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[Rho]", "(", 
    StyleBox["r",
     FontWeight->"Bold"], ")"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3c5ca045-dcbf-4acd-9c89-8a3fbbc8c085"],
 "."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8149436888118744`*^9, 3.8149436977822976`*^9}, {
  3.8149437480299177`*^9, 3.814943749884426*^9}, {3.81494387973838*^9, 
  3.8149439342648263`*^9}, {3.814945013935299*^9, 
  3.8149450191022563`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"72b17139-137c-4c47-80f1-\
34cb82f46b2b"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Theorem 2", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944000553141*^9, 
  3.8149440018894424`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a9e1e623-c3f0-4d5d-8a44-\
7221ba4dd6a2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The energy of the system can be written as a functional of the density ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[Rho]", "(", 
    StyleBox["r",
     FontWeight->"Bold"], ")"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f099839d-dabe-46f3-b39f-2763d52f048b"],
 ". For an external potential ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["v", "ext"], "(", 
    StyleBox["r",
     FontWeight->"Bold"], ")"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7bfc9ae3-70e1-4786-b126-576b3a623241"],
 ", the exact ground-state energy ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"E", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["\[Rho]",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], 
     StyleBox["(",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], 
     StyleBox["r",
      FontWeight->"Bold"], ")"}], "]"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f36f7062-a47b-41cc-986c-7f71662111e1"],
 " is given by the global minimum value of this functional. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944047989253*^9, 3.814944088843056*^9}, {
  3.8149441195148735`*^9, 3.814944242370001*^9}, {3.8149450220449233`*^9, 
  3.814945039714983*^9}, {3.814945097778695*^9, 
  3.8149450983129673`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"444b306f-07c2-4a97-bf63-\
cf776501644e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A functional is just a function that depends on a function. This theorem \
indicates that if the energy is minimized by a variational method by \
modifying the density ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[Rho]", "(", 
    StyleBox["r",
     FontWeight->"Bold"], ")"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "557d9ef4-5323-440a-94b6-26880807c6d3"],
 ", the lowest achievable energy will be the best approximation to the ground \
state of the system. If we find the true global minimum energy of the \
functional, this value will be the exact ground-state energy of the system."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944250209524*^9, 3.814944374273843*^9}, {
  3.814945103925652*^9, 
  3.814945105799241*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0b3b0b54-dd27-4d26-9768-\
5e2b9e811f9a"],

Cell["Usually, the energy functional is written in the form", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8149445550495024`*^9, 
  3.8149445673712826`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"902847ca-33ac-4280-a434-\
6630b6c65b0a"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["E",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["[",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["\[Rho]",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], 
    StyleBox[
     RowBox[{"(", 
      StyleBox["r",
       FontWeight->"Bold"], ")"}],
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
   StyleBox["]",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["F",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["[",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["\[Rho]",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], 
     StyleBox[
      RowBox[{"(", 
       StyleBox["r",
        FontWeight->"Bold"], ")"}],
      FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
    StyleBox["]",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
   StyleBox["+",
    FontSlant->"Plain"], 
   RowBox[{"\[Integral]", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox[
      StyleBox["v",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], 
      StyleBox["ext",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      StyleBox["r",
       FontWeight->"Bold",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}], "\[Rho]", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      StyleBox["r",
       FontWeight->"Bold",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}], 
     RowBox[{"\[DifferentialD]", 
      StyleBox["r",
       FontWeight->"Bold",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8149445802763047`*^9, 3.8149446687645245`*^9}, {
  3.8149450430265093`*^9, 
  3.8149450893114443`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e6ddc5e4-b6d8-4432-b65b-\
b18ad141d340"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["F",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["[",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["\[Rho]",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], 
     StyleBox["(",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["r",
      FontWeight->"Bold",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox[")",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
    StyleBox["]",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b867f82a-f4f0-45a8-b29f-c67c63e5f277"],
 " is some unknown, universal functional of the electron density."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944672899276*^9, 3.814944673411477*^9}, {
  3.814944715637702*^9, 3.8149447386544056`*^9}, {3.814945082219493*^9, 
  3.814945082219493*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"de7e3204-2db8-4f24-88ad-\
63dcefba6bc2"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Finding the Density Functional", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944767302372*^9, 
  3.814944773454214*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"48d664ca-a537-4bc0-8e02-\
0cb418a1f49e"],

Cell["\<\
We need some way to find the form of the density functional. Recall that the \
electronic Hamiltonian (neglecting internuclear repulsion) takes the form\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8149447766112933`*^9, 3.81494485539705*^9}, 
   3.8149449653277617`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"7043f032-2c83-491e-ab20-\
835ad6735ed8"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SubscriptBox[
   OverscriptBox[
    StyleBox["H",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], "e"], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    OverscriptBox[
     StyleBox["T",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], 
    StyleBox["e",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "+", 
   SubscriptBox[
    OverscriptBox[
     StyleBox["V",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], 
    StyleBox["eN",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "+", 
   SubscriptBox[
    OverscriptBox[
     StyleBox["V",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], 
    StyleBox["ee",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 
  3.814944934511548*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"320be1d1-4fbc-4603-8383-\
73c134e6abe9"],

Cell["\<\
If we now represent our energy as dependent on the electron density function \
\[Rho], we can then write\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8149449712891912`*^9, 3.814944987515238*^9}, {
  3.814945119445777*^9, 3.814945125192292*^9}, {3.8149451623258457`*^9, 
  3.8149451686076202`*^9}, {3.815051115444441*^9, 
  3.8150511155672364`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b5a0d485-c6c7-420e-a989-\
7c5197d97ff7"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["E",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["[",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "\[Rho]", "]"}], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["T",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["e",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["E",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["eN",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["E",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["ee",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", "\[Rho]", 
    "]"}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
  3.81494513302932*^9, 3.8149452103655367`*^9}, {3.814946643168869*^9, 
  3.814946650162446*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"667ae4d5-dc1c-43c6-a8e4-\
ce95e6787acd"],

Cell["\<\
We know that the electron-nuclear interaction term should take the form\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8149453204440403`*^9, 
  3.8149453463589087`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c1998c69-96d3-4423-ac8b-\
efb7bf557a97"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["E",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["eN",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}], 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  RowBox[{
   UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
    StyleBox["A",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   RowBox[{"\[Integral]", 
    RowBox[{
     FractionBox[
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["Z",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], 
        StyleBox["A",
         FontSlant->"Italic"]], "\[Rho]", 
       RowBox[{"(", 
        StyleBox["r",
         FontWeight->"Bold",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}]}], 
      RowBox[{"|", 
       RowBox[{
        StyleBox["r",
         FontWeight->"Bold",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "-", 
        SubscriptBox[
         StyleBox["R",
          FontWeight->"Bold",
          FontSlant->"Italic"], 
         StyleBox["A",
          FontSlant->"Italic"]]}], "|"}]], 
     RowBox[{"\[DifferentialD]", 
      StyleBox["r",
       FontWeight->"Bold",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8149445802763047`*^9, 3.8149446687645245`*^9}, {
  3.8149450430265093`*^9, 3.8149450893114443`*^9}, {3.8149453558985553`*^9, 
  3.814945367938826*^9}, {3.814945412530137*^9, 3.814945484885168*^9}, {
  3.814946659361224*^9, 
  3.8149466601368933`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a01ad5f2-c371-4b3e-83f7-\
5cefebd33c2e"],

Cell["\<\
and we can write the form of the interaction of the electron density with \
itself, a sort of self-coulomb repulsion,\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814945498253469*^9, 
  3.814945535651699*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d5011373-7d40-4b94-a2c4-\
0dd66476ca44"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["J",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}], 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox["1", "2"], 
   RowBox[{"\[Integral]", 
    RowBox[{"\[Integral]", 
     RowBox[{
      FractionBox[
       RowBox[{"\[Rho]", 
        RowBox[{"(", 
         StyleBox["r",
          FontWeight->"Bold",
          FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}], "\[Rho]", 
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{
          StyleBox["r",
           FontWeight->"Bold",
           FontSlant->"Italic"], "'"}], ")"}]}], 
       RowBox[{"|", 
        RowBox[{
         StyleBox["r",
          FontWeight->"Bold",
          FontSlant->"Italic"], "-", 
         RowBox[{
          StyleBox["r",
           FontWeight->"Bold",
           FontSlant->"Italic"], "'"}]}], "|"}]], 
      RowBox[{"\[DifferentialD]", 
       StyleBox["r",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
      RowBox[{"\[DifferentialD]", 
       RowBox[{
        StyleBox["r",
         FontWeight->"Bold",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "'"}]}]}]}]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8149445802763047`*^9, 3.8149446687645245`*^9}, {
  3.8149450430265093`*^9, 3.8149450893114443`*^9}, {3.8149453558985553`*^9, 
  3.814945367938826*^9}, {3.814945412530137*^9, 3.814945484885168*^9}, {
  3.8149455566739254`*^9, 3.814945599943204*^9}, {3.814974125416725*^9, 
  3.8149741295923214`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d89b84c8-76fc-4a9d-9d81-\
89d206932e0f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "But so far, we don\[CloseCurlyQuote]t know the form of the density \
functional, and we don\[CloseCurlyQuote]t know the form of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["T",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["e",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
   3.81494513302932*^9, 3.8149452103655367`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "4c542812-3469-4968-aab8-59ecabc192e0"],
 "or the full form of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["V",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["ee",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
   3.81494513302932*^9, 3.8149452103655367`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "3bc4d697-8d16-4b60-9be6-07f4c13e5146"],
 "."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.81494561021672*^9, 
  3.8149456440323706`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"908d692b-3d7e-4adb-bddb-\
db2de8d20521"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Kohn-Sham DFT", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8149457271560583`*^9, 
  3.814945731791072*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"db3d6196-a068-4486-b47c-\
87d759931aca"],

Cell["\<\
The Kohn-Sham approach to solving the problem of the electron density is to \
assume that the ground-state density of an interacting system can be \
represented by solving some equal non-interacting system where the electrons \
move in a single-particle potential. This approach is something like the \
Hartree approximation for a standard wavefunction; now the density can be \
written as a Slater determinant wavefunction,\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8149459670300627`*^9, 3.81494607276342*^9}, {
  3.8149461239714837`*^9, 3.8149461432259755`*^9}, {3.8149463705053844`*^9, 
  3.814946372799841*^9}, {3.8149464056764965`*^9, 
  3.814946419626181*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0558f9fc-b047-42b3-b966-\
db52da6fcfd5"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SubscriptBox["\[Psi]", 
   StyleBox["KS",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox["1", 
    SqrtBox[
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["N",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "!"}]]], 
   RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["\[Chi]", "1"], 
       RowBox[{"(", 
        SubscriptBox[
         StyleBox["x",
          FontWeight->"Bold",
          FontSlant->"Italic"], "1"], ")"}], 
       SubscriptBox["\[Chi]", "2"], 
       RowBox[{"(", 
        SubscriptBox[
         StyleBox["x",
          FontWeight->"Bold",
          FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], ")"}]}], "..."}], 
     SubscriptBox["\[Chi]", 
      StyleBox["N",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["x",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox["N",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]], ")"}]}], 
    "\[RightBracketingBar]"}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.810112811439228*^9, 3.8101128248442793`*^9}, {
   3.810479494926491*^9, 3.8104795038498344`*^9}, {3.810479572543576*^9, 
   3.8104796147383184`*^9}, {3.8104802055659895`*^9, 
   3.8104802433915305`*^9}, {3.8104802785189395`*^9, 
   3.8104802814214115`*^9}, {3.8109915300785556`*^9, 
   3.8109916793993816`*^9}, {3.810991710031681*^9, 3.8109918292023373`*^9}, {
   3.810994488524798*^9, 3.810994499853472*^9}, {3.8109948928195066`*^9, 
   3.8109948950763626`*^9}, {3.8109949491606197`*^9, 3.810995087249513*^9}, {
   3.8109951188614283`*^9, 3.8109951226144466`*^9}, {3.8115998145208507`*^9, 
   3.8115999093225703`*^9}, 3.8119468581508093`*^9, {3.8126173912859564`*^9, 
   3.8126174353481674`*^9}, {3.812617986792708*^9, 3.812617987701547*^9}, {
   3.8126194925193796`*^9, 3.812619503416272*^9}, {3.812619551056244*^9, 
   3.812619564308283*^9}, {3.812619992990877*^9, 3.8126200208718753`*^9}, 
   3.8126201248430705`*^9, {3.812620163920018*^9, 3.8126201669704065`*^9}, {
   3.8126204678526173`*^9, 3.8126204826728334`*^9}, {3.8126205155312433`*^9, 
   3.81262057853043*^9}, {3.812620660711446*^9, 3.812620661159943*^9}, {
   3.8126208302516937`*^9, 3.8126208466299543`*^9}, {3.812620980916898*^9, 
   3.8126209810859137`*^9}, 3.8126287856964226`*^9, {3.812629271581931*^9, 
   3.8126292755855017`*^9}, {3.8126293423208475`*^9, 3.812629351460653*^9}, {
   3.8126294501142464`*^9, 3.8126295143102984`*^9}, {3.8126295903225517`*^9, 
   3.812629649928158*^9}, {3.8126296948107743`*^9, 3.812629695292021*^9}, {
   3.8126300281015587`*^9, 3.81263005763659*^9}, {3.812630089427315*^9, 
   3.8126301336773043`*^9}, {3.8126301819630384`*^9, 3.8126302619488583`*^9}, 
   3.8126308057010317`*^9, {3.8126309591900663`*^9, 3.8126309614862156`*^9}, {
   3.8126311639264126`*^9, 3.812631166180791*^9}, {3.812631430624729*^9, 
   3.8126314355789146`*^9}, {3.8126314742473674`*^9, 3.812631489219202*^9}, {
   3.8126315261200433`*^9, 3.8126315361274185`*^9}, {3.8149464782766204`*^9, 
   3.8149465233109627`*^9}, {3.8149736889622183`*^9, 
   3.8149736954529533`*^9}, {3.814973732021331*^9, 
   3.8149737699985886`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e88e922b-5ef8-489d-bc60-\
4c76209b7309"],

Cell["\<\
and we can solve the problem by an approach analogous to the Hartree-Fock \
method!\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814946543568231*^9, 
  3.814946567299901*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4e537e40-5850-4229-a976-\
aabd4a0b362d"],

Cell["In the Kohn-Sham approach, the energy is given by", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8149465957220116`*^9, 
  3.8149466021757364`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b6815159-9c44-4465-8131-\
7cc01672feeb"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["E",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["[",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "\[Rho]", "]"}], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["T",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["s",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["E",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["eN",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["J",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["E",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["xc",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", "\[Rho]", 
    "]"}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
  3.81494513302932*^9, 3.8149452103655367`*^9}, {3.8149466202350535`*^9, 
  3.8149466212674627`*^9}, {3.814946665059575*^9, 3.814946692804378*^9}, {
  3.814946774093356*^9, 
  3.814946782953416*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"06d0bc9a-f26f-43f6-ba5f-\
32bcdc747f92"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["T",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["s",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
   3.81494513302932*^9, 3.8149452103655367`*^9}, {3.8149466202350535`*^9, 
   3.8149466212674627`*^9}, {3.814946665059575*^9, 3.814946692804378*^9}, {
   3.814946774093356*^9, 3.814946782953416*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "b144d9a0-a845-4547-abe5-302127589f5d"],
 " is the Kohn-Sham kinetic energy, representing the kinetic energy of a \
non-interacting electron gas, and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["E",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["xc",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
   3.81494513302932*^9, 3.8149452103655367`*^9}, {3.8149466202350535`*^9, 
   3.8149466212674627`*^9}, {3.814946665059575*^9, 3.814946692804378*^9}, {
   3.814946774093356*^9, 3.814946782953416*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "d6b68095-0f58-4ca7-a59d-be9fea5d7623"],
 "is the exchange-correlation energy functional, which can be defined as "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814946785686612*^9, 3.814946860497774*^9}, {
  3.814947134470868*^9, 
  3.814947135437705*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"614c8dc4-f52e-4201-8558-\
834faeac1135"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["E",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["xc",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["T",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}], "-", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["T",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox["s",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}]}], ")"}], "+", 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["E",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox["ee",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}], "-", 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["J",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}]}], 
    ")"}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
  3.81494513302932*^9, 3.8149452103655367`*^9}, {3.8149466202350535`*^9, 
  3.8149466212674627`*^9}, {3.814946665059575*^9, 3.814946692804378*^9}, {
  3.814946774093356*^9, 3.814946782953416*^9}, {3.8149468676382875`*^9, 
  3.8149468690861945`*^9}, {3.8149469033830104`*^9, 
  3.81494694312879*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d6bb02c6-ced4-4e21-b868-\
e3061258c9b8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In other words, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["E",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["xc",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
   3.81494513302932*^9, 3.8149452103655367`*^9}, {3.8149466202350535`*^9, 
   3.8149466212674627`*^9}, {3.814946665059575*^9, 3.814946692804378*^9}, {
   3.814946774093356*^9, 3.814946782953416*^9}, {3.8149468676382875`*^9, 
   3.8149468690861945`*^9}, {3.8149469033830104`*^9, 3.81494694312879*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"47a6b68d-2190-4af1-9316-57ff781b48b7"],
 "represents all of the energy contributions that are not accounted for when \
we switch from the interacting picture of Hohenberg-Kohn to the \
non-interacting picture of Kohn-Sham. The problem is, we \
don\[CloseCurlyQuote]t know the form of this functional, and we can only use \
approximate forms. The difference between all of the many DFT methods is the \
approximate form of the exchange-correlation functional that they use."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8149469461356716`*^9, 
  3.8149471139395833`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"575a92c9-093c-4e9b-86b9-\
d823cdd6d736"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Solving for the Kohn-Sham Orbitals", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.81494730758447*^9, 3.8149473148667345`*^9}, {
  3.81494738898132*^9, 
  3.8149474438539085`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c7cd8621-ad48-4ed7-8329-\
15c00ac6ab47"],

Cell["\<\
As mentioned, the Kohn-Sham DFT approach closely resembles the Hartree-Fock \
method. Instead of the Fock operator, we have the Kohn-Sham Hamiltonian,\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814947454999415*^9, 3.8149474980237513`*^9}, {
  3.814973531827513*^9, 
  3.8149735619828033`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"437f0bac-ecef-4c0c-b210-\
9017ece162dd"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    OverscriptBox[
     StyleBox["h",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], 
    StyleBox["KS",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    StyleBox["r",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}], 
   SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", 
    StyleBox["i",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    StyleBox["r",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}]}], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", 
    StyleBox["i",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", 
    StyleBox["i",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    StyleBox["r",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
  3.814973609174138*^9, 3.814973622744397*^9}, {3.814973657938239*^9, 
  3.8149736650979123`*^9}, {3.8149737480555277`*^9, 
  3.814973820215623*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3f64f40f-7579-4698-a338-\
40a8814bcef0"],

Cell["\<\
Note that in this equation we\[CloseCurlyQuote]re only looking at spatial \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]orbitals\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], but the equation for \
both spin and spatial components would be similar. The Kohn-Sham Hamiltonian \
is given by\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8149738258899074`*^9, 
  3.814973878761538*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0bafe34f-dc6a-4a02-83d8-\
562fb6dec2dd"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    OverscriptBox[
     StyleBox["h",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], 
    StyleBox["KS",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    StyleBox["r",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}]}], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"-", 
     FractionBox["1", "2"]}], 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox["\[Del]", "2"], 
     RowBox[{"+", 
      SubscriptBox[
       OverscriptBox[
        StyleBox["V",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], 
       StyleBox["eN",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]}], 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     StyleBox["r",
      FontWeight->"Bold",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{"\[Integral]", 
    RowBox[{
     FractionBox[
      RowBox[{"\[Rho]", 
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{
         StyleBox["r",
          FontWeight->"Bold",
          FontSlant->"Italic"], "'"}], ")"}]}], 
      RowBox[{"|", 
       RowBox[{
        StyleBox["r",
         FontWeight->"Bold",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "-", 
        RowBox[{
         StyleBox["r",
          FontWeight->"Bold",
          FontSlant->"Italic"], "'"}]}], "|"}]], 
     RowBox[{"\[DifferentialD]", 
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["r",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "'"}]}]}]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     OverscriptBox[
      StyleBox["V",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], 
     StyleBox["xc",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     StyleBox["r",
      FontWeight->"Bold",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
   3.814973609174138*^9, 3.814973622744397*^9}, {3.814973657938239*^9, 
   3.8149736650979123`*^9}, {3.8149737480555277`*^9, 3.814973820215623*^9}, 
   3.814973885500003*^9, {3.8149739312427583`*^9, 3.814973945625701*^9}, {
   3.814973987537115*^9, 3.814974000973981*^9}, {3.814974038299629*^9, 
   3.8149740403493423`*^9}, {3.81497408506464*^9, 3.81497416428242*^9}, 
   3.814974217423894*^9},ExpressionUUID->"afbc00f6-00c2-42ed-bd6a-\
310ae05e74ac"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where the first term represents the kinetic energy operator of a \
non-interacting electron gas. Again, here, the form of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    OverscriptBox[
     StyleBox["V",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], 
    StyleBox["xc",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    StyleBox["r",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}]}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
    3.814973609174138*^9, 3.814973622744397*^9}, {3.814973657938239*^9, 
    3.8149736650979123`*^9}, {3.8149737480555277`*^9, 3.814973820215623*^9}, 
    3.814973885500003*^9, {3.8149739312427583`*^9, 3.814973945625701*^9}, {
    3.814973987537115*^9, 3.814974000973981*^9}, {3.814974038299629*^9, 
    3.8149740403493423`*^9}, {3.81497408506464*^9, 3.81497416428242*^9}, 
    3.814974217423894*^9},ExpressionUUID->
  "f94a6773-95d0-41e7-a677-25921c08f2d3"],
 "is unknown, so different DFT methods involve different approaches to \
approximate the form of this term."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814974208510536*^9, 3.8149742469468822`*^9}, {
  3.815046807284334*^9, 
  3.8150468356687512`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8aa05ce5-7ce0-474b-bf7a-\
e355d83e6042"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Because DFT has a similar formulation to Hartree-Fock, it has a similar \
computational cost. However, because correlation is taken into account \
through the exchange-correlation term, the accuracy can be much higher than \
Hartree-Fock. Note that this accuracy depends strongly on the form of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    OverscriptBox[
     StyleBox["V",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], 
    StyleBox["xc",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    StyleBox["r",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}]}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
    3.814973609174138*^9, 3.814973622744397*^9}, {3.814973657938239*^9, 
    3.8149736650979123`*^9}, {3.8149737480555277`*^9, 3.814973820215623*^9}, 
    3.814973885500003*^9, {3.8149739312427583`*^9, 3.814973945625701*^9}, {
    3.814973987537115*^9, 3.814974000973981*^9}, {3.814974038299629*^9, 
    3.8149740403493423`*^9}, {3.81497408506464*^9, 3.81497416428242*^9}, 
    3.814974217423894*^9},ExpressionUUID->
  "4b3c6a01-8703-40bd-a765-b45578892f0c"],
 ", and there is no systematic way to improve accuracy (unlike in \
post-Hartree-Fock methods). "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.815034708409008*^9, 3.8150347154984007`*^9}, {
  3.8150347480639806`*^9, 3.815034867847584*^9}, {3.815035527298959*^9, 
  3.8150355284582896`*^9}, {3.815046273914561*^9, 
  3.815046283309187*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0342cdcf-2161-4adc-a17c-\
3005ccfc24c6"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["The Exchange-Correlation Potential", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.81504651825054*^9, 
  3.8150465262793145`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"39fba0bc-a73b-42b5-860b-\
05d9c59dca06"],

Cell["\<\
We now want to find some form of the exchange-correlation potential that we \
can use to compute the electronic structure and energy of molecules. Let us \
first examine the exchange-correlation energy, separating the energy into \
exchange and correlation terms,\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.815046530056077*^9, 3.8150466505782943`*^9}, {
  3.815046747705806*^9, 3.815046748783098*^9}, {3.8150469542955103`*^9, 
  3.8150469981582594`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4cece146-ce4f-4cfd-aa76-\
d4358bc47eb0"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["E",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["xc",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["T",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}], "-", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["T",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox["s",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}]}], ")"}], "+", 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["E",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox["ee",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}], "-", 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["J",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}]}], 
    ")"}]}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{"\t    ", 
  RowBox[{"=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox[
      StyleBox["E",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], 
      StyleBox["c",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}], "+", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox[
      StyleBox["E",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], 
      StyleBox["x",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", "\[Rho]", 
     "]"}]}]}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{"\t    ", 
  RowBox[{"=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[Integral]", 
     RowBox[{"\[Rho]", 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       StyleBox["r",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}], 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", 
        StyleBox["c",
         FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", 
       RowBox[{"\[Rho]", 
        RowBox[{"(", 
         StyleBox["r",
          FontWeight->"Bold",
          FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}]}], "]"}], 
      RowBox[{"\[DifferentialD]", 
       StyleBox["r",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}]}], "+", 
    RowBox[{"\[Integral]", 
     RowBox[{"\[Rho]", 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       StyleBox["r",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}], 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", 
        StyleBox["x",
         FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", 
       RowBox[{"\[Rho]", 
        RowBox[{"(", 
         StyleBox["r",
          FontWeight->"Bold",
          FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}]}], "]"}], 
      RowBox[{"\[DifferentialD]", 
       StyleBox["r",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}]}]}]}]}]}], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
  3.81494513302932*^9, 3.8149452103655367`*^9}, {3.8149466202350535`*^9, 
  3.8149466212674627`*^9}, {3.814946665059575*^9, 3.814946692804378*^9}, {
  3.814946774093356*^9, 3.814946782953416*^9}, {3.8149468676382875`*^9, 
  3.8149468690861945`*^9}, {3.8149469033830104`*^9, 3.81494694312879*^9}, {
  3.81504701277137*^9, 3.8150471049973593`*^9}, {3.815047166699194*^9, 
  3.8150471672484417`*^9}, {3.8150472258869896`*^9, 3.8150472282064495`*^9}, {
  3.8150478795530877`*^9, 
  3.8150478952736435`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3cf7fa9a-f0b1-4180-8b4b-\
d418f57cfa1e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", 
   StyleBox["c",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
   3.81494513302932*^9, 3.8149452103655367`*^9}, {3.8149466202350535`*^9, 
   3.8149466212674627`*^9}, {3.814946665059575*^9, 3.814946692804378*^9}, {
   3.814946774093356*^9, 3.814946782953416*^9}, {3.8149468676382875`*^9, 
   3.8149468690861945`*^9}, {3.8149469033830104`*^9, 3.81494694312879*^9}, {
   3.81504701277137*^9, 3.8150471049973593`*^9}, {3.815047166699194*^9, 
   3.8150471672484417`*^9}, {3.8150472258869896`*^9, 3.8150472282064495`*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"2f65e647-31f4-4a12-a190-eaa9e12df604"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", 
   StyleBox["x",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
   3.81494513302932*^9, 3.8149452103655367`*^9}, {3.8149466202350535`*^9, 
   3.8149466212674627`*^9}, {3.814946665059575*^9, 3.814946692804378*^9}, {
   3.814946774093356*^9, 3.814946782953416*^9}, {3.8149468676382875`*^9, 
   3.8149468690861945`*^9}, {3.8149469033830104`*^9, 3.81494694312879*^9}, {
   3.81504701277137*^9, 3.8150471049973593`*^9}, {3.815047166699194*^9, 
   3.8150471672484417`*^9}, {3.8150472258869896`*^9, 3.8150472282064495`*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"f1b59897-bad4-4879-a7f4-8c4447ff9bb6"],
 " are the correlation and exchange energy per particle, respectively. Note \
that these are also functionals of the density."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.81504723122009*^9, 3.815047255234138*^9}, {
  3.815047980148121*^9, 
  3.8150479877318416`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"dc8f13b1-4704-4253-a323-\
592447917cf7"],

Cell["\<\
The relationship between the exchange-correlation energy and the \
exchange-correlation potential is given by the equation\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.8150469566100683`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"b3fb7779-cd2c-4bb0-805b-\
3a9b6b6ebbe9"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["V",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["xc",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}], "=", 
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox[
      StyleBox["E",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], 
      StyleBox["xc",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}]}], 
   RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", "\[Rho]"}]]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
  3.81494513302932*^9, 3.8149452103655367`*^9}, {3.8149466202350535`*^9, 
  3.8149466212674627`*^9}, {3.814946665059575*^9, 3.814946692804378*^9}, {
  3.814946774093356*^9, 3.814946782953416*^9}, {3.8149468676382875`*^9, 
  3.8149468690861945`*^9}, {3.8149469033830104`*^9, 3.81494694312879*^9}, {
  3.8150466748147345`*^9, 
  3.8150467387520385`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"47a64845-05cd-4b32-b188-\
5a48d4625598"],

Cell["\<\
Again, the goal of different DFT methods is to find the most accurate \
possible form of this exchange-correlation energy (and thus potential) that \
is computationally tractable.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8150482288345985`*^9, 
  3.815048275420519*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6f5522d4-36bc-47c7-b9a8-\
9e3f46b1e77a"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Classes of DFT Exchange-Correlation Functionals", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.815048196979351*^9, 
  3.8150482107440505`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8f611fc8-e57a-40b8-a3cc-\
894160f1a5f4"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Local Density Approximation (LDA) Functionals", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8150482147012863`*^9, 3.8150482235739827`*^9}, {
  3.8150488984826603`*^9, 
  3.8150488999413524`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a82630cc-7090-4443-9c0b-\
d43b0a847cc0"],

Cell["\<\
One of the first exchange-correlation energy forms developed is known as the \
local density approximation (LDA). In the LDA, the exchange and correlation \
terms are based on a uniform gas model. Importantly, the exchange \
contribution depends only on the magnitude of the electron density at a given \
point in space. In equation form, this is sometimes represented as\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.815048279537507*^9, 3.8150483604225864`*^9}, {
  3.8150483972787285`*^9, 
  3.815048497182048*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"955a4c39-7337-4f7d-915c-\
146108e3ddd8"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   SubsuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["E",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["x",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "LDA"], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}], "=", 
  RowBox[{"\[Integral]", 
   RowBox[{"\[Rho]", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     StyleBox["r",
      FontWeight->"Bold",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}], 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", 
      StyleBox["x",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", 
     RowBox[{"\[Rho]", 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       StyleBox["r",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}]}], "]"}], 
    RowBox[{"\[DifferentialD]", 
     StyleBox["r",
      FontWeight->"Bold",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
  3.81494513302932*^9, 3.8149452103655367`*^9}, {3.8149466202350535`*^9, 
  3.8149466212674627`*^9}, {3.814946665059575*^9, 3.814946692804378*^9}, {
  3.814946774093356*^9, 3.814946782953416*^9}, {3.8149468676382875`*^9, 
  3.8149468690861945`*^9}, {3.8149469033830104`*^9, 3.81494694312879*^9}, {
  3.81504701277137*^9, 3.8150471049973593`*^9}, {3.815047166699194*^9, 
  3.8150471672484417`*^9}, {3.8150472258869896`*^9, 3.8150472282064495`*^9}, {
  3.8150478795530877`*^9, 3.8150478952736435`*^9}, {3.8150485114024315`*^9, 
  3.8150485266035337`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ad90ca45-b1c0-4987-a4ea-\
159d62072b32"],

Cell["\<\
More exactly, the energy is given by the Dirac electron gas model as \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.815048539090906*^9, 
  3.815048566649371*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1b949674-fc1b-458f-b800-\
fb33dd192d1e"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   SubsuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["E",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["x",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "LDA"], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"-", 
    StyleBox["c",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
   RowBox[{"\[Integral]", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox["\[Rho]", 
      RowBox[{"4", "/", "3"}]], 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      StyleBox["r",
       FontWeight->"Bold",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}], 
     RowBox[{"\[DifferentialD]", 
      StyleBox["r",
       FontWeight->"Bold",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
  3.81494513302932*^9, 3.8149452103655367`*^9}, {3.8149466202350535`*^9, 
  3.8149466212674627`*^9}, {3.814946665059575*^9, 3.814946692804378*^9}, {
  3.814946774093356*^9, 3.814946782953416*^9}, {3.8149468676382875`*^9, 
  3.8149468690861945`*^9}, {3.8149469033830104`*^9, 3.81494694312879*^9}, {
  3.81504701277137*^9, 3.8150471049973593`*^9}, {3.815047166699194*^9, 
  3.8150471672484417`*^9}, {3.8150472258869896`*^9, 3.8150472282064495`*^9}, {
  3.8150478795530877`*^9, 3.8150478952736435`*^9}, {3.8150485114024315`*^9, 
  3.8150485266035337`*^9}, {3.815048603517369*^9, 3.8150486051811376`*^9}, {
  3.8150486379965525`*^9, 
  3.8150486453586044`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"47314fe4-bd3c-401e-8856-\
b983d084a6c8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where ",
 StyleBox["c",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is a constant. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.815048660068389*^9, 
  3.815048696526251*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9638d935-8a85-4d42-802b-\
9d75be5bb92a"],

Cell["\<\
This approximation is not used very often in modern research because it gives \
inaccurate results for both the exchange and correlation components of the \
energy.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8150487009036474`*^9, 
  3.81504872900136*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"dc184913-5403-4fd1-85c5-\
8bf379490933"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Generalized Gradient Approximation (GGA) Functionals", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8150487383473034`*^9, 3.8150487498779936`*^9}, {
  3.8150489013236475`*^9, 
  3.8150489025640025`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"41243f91-22e2-4e1e-a522-\
55761bbc2aac"],

Cell["\<\
In reality, the electron density in molecules can change rapidly over a short \
distance, so the homogeneous electron gas model doesn\[CloseCurlyQuote]t work \
very well. To correct for this reality, the generalized gradient \
approximation assumes that the exchange contribution to the energy depends \
not only on the electron density at a given point in space but also on its \
gradient, or rate of change. In equation form, we can make this relationship \
more clear by writing\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8150487595950794`*^9, 3.8150488471116424`*^9}, {
  3.815048924673376*^9, 
  3.8150489344087944`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"cd690cf5-84bc-400c-aa0c-\
fca9c86513c2"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   SubsuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["E",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["x",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "GGA"], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}], "=", 
  RowBox[{"\[Integral]", 
   RowBox[{"\[Rho]", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     StyleBox["r",
      FontWeight->"Bold",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}], 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", 
      StyleBox["x",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]], "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"\[Rho]", 
       RowBox[{"(", 
        StyleBox["r",
         FontWeight->"Bold",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}]}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"\[Del]", "\[Rho]"}]}], "]"}], 
    RowBox[{"\[DifferentialD]", 
     StyleBox["r",
      FontWeight->"Bold",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
  3.81494513302932*^9, 3.8149452103655367`*^9}, {3.8149466202350535`*^9, 
  3.8149466212674627`*^9}, {3.814946665059575*^9, 3.814946692804378*^9}, {
  3.814946774093356*^9, 3.814946782953416*^9}, {3.8149468676382875`*^9, 
  3.8149468690861945`*^9}, {3.8149469033830104`*^9, 3.81494694312879*^9}, {
  3.81504701277137*^9, 3.8150471049973593`*^9}, {3.815047166699194*^9, 
  3.8150471672484417`*^9}, {3.8150472258869896`*^9, 3.8150472282064495`*^9}, {
  3.8150478795530877`*^9, 3.8150478952736435`*^9}, {3.8150485114024315`*^9, 
  3.8150485266035337`*^9}, {3.815048941328576*^9, 3.8150489560758443`*^9}, {
  3.815048989576298*^9, 
  3.8150489928830914`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"675caf83-3dbb-461e-9319-\
1a7a118330fd"],

Cell["\<\
Sometimes, these functionals represent a mix of different components for the \
exchange terms (such as B88, also called B) and correlation terms (for \
example, LYP). BYLP would be an example of a full GGA functional. Other \
methods include PBE and PW91 (which also require some selection of the \
correlation functionals). Unfortunately, even with this improved \
approximation, these functionals still cannot produce a sufficiently accurate \
exchange contribution, so they are also not used so often.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.815049086789457*^9, 3.8150492387050242`*^9}, {
  3.8150493161659703`*^9, 3.815049370527198*^9}, {3.815049530229925*^9, 
  3.815049611825519*^9}, {3.8150518865592413`*^9, 
  3.815051887057385*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"40c3b5c4-05b1-45b0-aa15-\
9b2578af21ac"],

Cell["\<\
There are also meta-GGA functionals, in which the exchange-correlation energy \
depends also on the Laplacian (second derivative) of the electron density. \
Examples of such functionals include TPSS and M06L. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8150505499948196`*^9, 3.8150505616629677`*^9}, {
  3.8150506442376184`*^9, 
  3.81505069556399*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"50eefda7-cae7-47d6-b940-\
36c396cf1005"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Hybrid Methods", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.815049380837842*^9, 
  3.8150493840060987`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d846baed-dfd6-4bdc-a4e3-\
54383efbdd26"],

Cell["\<\
By far the most commonly utilized DFT methods utilize hybrid functionals. In \
short, these methods incorporate a portion of exchange from the Hartree-Fock \
method into the exchange-correlation energy obtained from an LDA or GGA \
functional. For example, the famous B3LYP exchange-correlation energy is \
given by\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8150496335252*^9, 3.8150496528611727`*^9}, {
   3.815049694897452*^9, 3.815049840171441*^9}, {3.8150503967240734`*^9, 
   3.815050437239769*^9}, 
   3.829307588769421*^9},ExpressionUUID->"bd2776fc-9d68-4841-8353-\
d62e7c40b574"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   SubsuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["E",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["xc",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "B3LYP"], "[", "\[Rho]", "]"}], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   SubsuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["E",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["x",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "LDA"], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["a",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "0"], 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SubsuperscriptBox[
       StyleBox["E",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox["x",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "HF"], "-", 
      SubsuperscriptBox[
       StyleBox["E",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox["x",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "LDA"]}], ")"}]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox[
     SubscriptBox[
      StyleBox["a",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "x"],
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["(",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     RowBox[{
      SubsuperscriptBox[
       StyleBox["E",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox["x",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "GGA"], "-", 
      SubsuperscriptBox[
       StyleBox["E",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox["x",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "LDA"]}], ")"}]}], "+", 
   SubsuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["E",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["c",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "LDA"], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["a",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["c",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SubsuperscriptBox[
       StyleBox["E",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "c", "GGA"], "-", 
      SubsuperscriptBox[
       StyleBox["E",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "c", "LDA"]}], 
     ")"}]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
  3.81494513302932*^9, 3.8149452103655367`*^9}, {3.8149466202350535`*^9, 
  3.8149466212674627`*^9}, {3.814946665059575*^9, 3.814946692804378*^9}, {
  3.814946774093356*^9, 3.814946782953416*^9}, {3.8149468676382875`*^9, 
  3.8149468690861945`*^9}, {3.8149469033830104`*^9, 3.81494694312879*^9}, {
  3.81504701277137*^9, 3.8150471049973593`*^9}, {3.815047166699194*^9, 
  3.8150471672484417`*^9}, {3.8150472258869896`*^9, 3.8150472282064495`*^9}, {
  3.8150478795530877`*^9, 3.8150478952736435`*^9}, {3.8150485114024315`*^9, 
  3.8150485266035337`*^9}, {3.815048941328576*^9, 3.8150489560758443`*^9}, {
  3.815048989576298*^9, 3.8150489928830914`*^9}, {3.815049848426564*^9, 
  3.8150499328589478`*^9}, {3.8150499751422405`*^9, 
  3.8150501369692917`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"837c913c-dc54-4ce0-98d7-\
f166607b6cf0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["a",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "0"]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
   3.81494513302932*^9, 3.8149452103655367`*^9}, {3.8149466202350535`*^9, 
   3.8149466212674627`*^9}, {3.814946665059575*^9, 3.814946692804378*^9}, {
   3.814946774093356*^9, 3.814946782953416*^9}, {3.8149468676382875`*^9, 
   3.8149468690861945`*^9}, {3.8149469033830104`*^9, 3.81494694312879*^9}, {
   3.81504701277137*^9, 3.8150471049973593`*^9}, {3.815047166699194*^9, 
   3.8150471672484417`*^9}, {3.8150472258869896`*^9, 
   3.8150472282064495`*^9}, {3.8150478795530877`*^9, 
   3.8150478952736435`*^9}, {3.8150485114024315`*^9, 
   3.8150485266035337`*^9}, {3.815048941328576*^9, 3.8150489560758443`*^9}, {
   3.815048989576298*^9, 3.8150489928830914`*^9}, {3.815049848426564*^9, 
   3.8150499328589478`*^9}, {3.8150499751422405`*^9, 3.8150501369692917`*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"53092d41-e053-4d6b-8cbf-187f8be06c06"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["a",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "x"],
   FontSlant->"Italic"]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
   3.81494513302932*^9, 3.8149452103655367`*^9}, {3.8149466202350535`*^9, 
   3.8149466212674627`*^9}, {3.814946665059575*^9, 3.814946692804378*^9}, {
   3.814946774093356*^9, 3.814946782953416*^9}, {3.8149468676382875`*^9, 
   3.8149468690861945`*^9}, {3.8149469033830104`*^9, 3.81494694312879*^9}, {
   3.81504701277137*^9, 3.8150471049973593`*^9}, {3.815047166699194*^9, 
   3.8150471672484417`*^9}, {3.8150472258869896`*^9, 
   3.8150472282064495`*^9}, {3.8150478795530877`*^9, 
   3.8150478952736435`*^9}, {3.8150485114024315`*^9, 
   3.8150485266035337`*^9}, {3.815048941328576*^9, 3.8150489560758443`*^9}, {
   3.815048989576298*^9, 3.8150489928830914`*^9}, {3.815049848426564*^9, 
   3.8150499328589478`*^9}, {3.8150499751422405`*^9, 3.8150501369692917`*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"5fbc9d3b-5af3-4674-83e7-8c2b4fcdb360"],
 ", and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["a",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["c",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.814944864357977*^9, 3.814944934511548*^9}, {
   3.81494513302932*^9, 3.8149452103655367`*^9}, {3.8149466202350535`*^9, 
   3.8149466212674627`*^9}, {3.814946665059575*^9, 3.814946692804378*^9}, {
   3.814946774093356*^9, 3.814946782953416*^9}, {3.8149468676382875`*^9, 
   3.8149468690861945`*^9}, {3.8149469033830104`*^9, 3.81494694312879*^9}, {
   3.81504701277137*^9, 3.8150471049973593`*^9}, {3.815047166699194*^9, 
   3.8150471672484417`*^9}, {3.8150472258869896`*^9, 
   3.8150472282064495`*^9}, {3.8150478795530877`*^9, 
   3.8150478952736435`*^9}, {3.8150485114024315`*^9, 
   3.8150485266035337`*^9}, {3.815048941328576*^9, 3.8150489560758443`*^9}, {
   3.815048989576298*^9, 3.8150489928830914`*^9}, {3.815049848426564*^9, 
   3.8150499328589478`*^9}, {3.8150499751422405`*^9, 3.8150501369692917`*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"c8973f2d-431a-4ce9-9da2-72d0a47290a6"],
 " are constants optimized empirically."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8150501409639316`*^9, 
  3.8150501577720385`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5be1404d-d18f-4871-939d-\
e0aaccfd2c51"],

Cell["\<\
There are many other examples of hybrid functionals, for example PBE0, \
\[Omega]B97X, TPSSh, M06-2X, etc. Each have their own unique formulations for \
mixing the Hartree-Fock exchange with the GGA or LDA exchange and may also \
differ in the correlation potential. Again, there\[CloseCurlyQuote]s no \
hierarchy to which of these may be more or less accurate, and it may depend \
on the system being studied.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8150502048109016`*^9, 3.815050208485796*^9}, {
  3.8150502486399975`*^9, 3.8150502502917767`*^9}, {3.8150502998030024`*^9, 
  3.8150503852682037`*^9}, {3.8150504450634575`*^9, 3.8150505008979445`*^9}, {
  3.8150505645443354`*^9, 3.815050571119192*^9}, {3.8150506391448135`*^9, 
  3.8150506393170614`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e1321116-45c1-48c1-b254-\
780ce9e59b5a"],

Cell["\<\
More recently, double-hybrid methods have been developed that also \
incorporate an MP2-like contribution to the correlation energy. These methods \
are typically more accurate, but they sacrifice the computational efficiency \
of DFT by requiring MP2 calculations.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8150507638610973`*^9, 3.815050820952388*^9}, {
  3.815052054057457*^9, 
  3.8150520571019897`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"078a21bd-d18f-411f-8ace-\
226b6713670f"],

Cell["", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c5b44b54-19c5-4743-a09c-32c8e238dfc0"],

Cell["", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"18fdf5d3-d503-4cf4-8357-6e135fc889c3"],

Cell["", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"692b53dc-7907-4669-ac7b-09a4a100e58a"],

Cell["", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9a3f6fa1-b471-4db0-822c-8ea3b624c29e"],

Cell["", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"132e1cda-b6d4-4b00-b024-80d1468ed0ae"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
},
